A 33-year-old man has been arrested for allegedly shooting and wounding a 11-year-old girl on his farm in Swartruggens in the North West.Police spokesperson Sabata Mokgwabone said the suspect handed himself over to police. The suspect will be charged with attempted murder and will appear before the local magistrate court on Monday, Mokgwabone said.The incident comes after a 16-year-old boy was allegedly murdered by farmworkers just two months ago at another farm in Coligny in the North West.Mokgwabone added that by the time the parents took their daughter to hospital the bullet was still stuck in her arm.-TNA Reporter